text: The 2001–02 Israeli Noar Leumit League was the 8th season since its introduction in 1994 as the top-tier football in Israel for teenagers between the ages 18–20. Maccabi Tel Aviv won the title, whilst Maccabi Netanya and Maccabi Herzliya were relegated. ==Final table== ==External links== *Noar Premier League 01-02 One.co.il Category:Israeli Noar Premier League seasons Youth
